{meta: title Days Of Sand And Shovels}
{meta: artist Charley Pride}
{meta: composer Bud Reneau and Doyle Marsh}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]When I noticed her the first time
[A7]I was outside runnin' barefoot in the [D7]rain
[G7]She lived in the house next door
[C]Her nose was pressed against the window pane
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
When I looked at her she smiled
[A7]And showed a place where two teeth used to [D7]be
[G7]And I heard her ask her mom
[C]If she could come outside and play with me
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
Soon the days of sand and shovels
[A7]Gave way to the mysteries of [D7]life
[G7]Then I noticed she was changin'
[C]And I looked at her through different eyes
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
We became as one and knew
[A7]A love without beginning or an [D7]end
[G7]Every day I lived with her
[C]Was like a new day dawning once again
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
[Dm]And I've loved her since every doll was Shirley Temple
[A#7]Soda pop was still a nickel
[D]Jam was on her fingertips
[G7]Milk was circled on her lips
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 6}
[C]After many years our love grew [A7]silent
[D7]And at night I heard her cry
[G7]And when she left me in the fall
[C]I said that it would be our last goodbye
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 7}
I was man enough to give her
[A7]Everything she needed for a [D7]home
[G7]In searching for a perfect love I found
[C]That I could not give her a child
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 8}
Now she lives a quiet life
[A7]And is the mother of a little [D7]girl
[G7]Every time I pass her house
[C]My thoughts go back into another world
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 9}
Because I see her little girl
[A7]Her nose is pressed against the window [D7]pane
[G7]She thinks I'm a lonely man
[C]Who wants to come inside out of the rain
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 10}
[Dm]And I've loved her since every doll was Shirley Temple
[A#7]Soda pop was still a nickel
[D]Jam was on her fingertips
[G7]Milk was circled on her [C]lips
{end_of_verse}
